<TEXT>
   New York Giants linebacker Lawrence Taylor,
whose drug problem drew a one-month suspension last year, failed a
breath test and was arrested when a trooper found him asleep in his
car on the side of a highway.
   ``This was the first alcohol he has consumed in the last five
months and he got ill,'' said Steve Rosner, an agent who handles
Taylor's endorsements. ``He had a little bit of a family quarrel
and that led to him having a drink or two.''
   He said Taylor had parked early Friday along the side of the
Garden State Parkway.
   State police Sgt. Robert Kenyon declined to say whet level of
alcohol Taylor's test showed. ``He failed. They gave him a summons
for driving while intoxicated,'' said Kenyon.
   But Rosner said that according to the citation Taylor was given,
he did not exceed the 0.10 percent blood alcohol level considered
legally drunk under New Jersey law.
   Taylor, who entered a drug treatment program in 1986, was
released on his own recognizance, police said. His car was
impounded.
