<HEAD>Thief Caught Under Priest's Bed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who stole $25 worth of alms and three silver
hearts from a church in central Rome was arrested by police who
found him hiding under the parish priest's bed, the ANSA news
agency reported Saturday.
   The priest called police after he heard a noise in the rectory
of the church, known as Santa Maria in Campitelli.
   Police found the man with the money and the silver hearts in his
pockets, which he apparently stole minutes earlier, ANSA said.
   The hearts were offerings made to the church by parishoners who
sought God's intercession for a special favor.
