<FIRST>r i AM-Bangladesh     03-25 0102</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Bangladesh,0106</SECOND>
<HEAD>Government Releases Prisoners On Independence Eve</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government said it released 619
prisoners from jails across the country on Saturday, the eve of the
anniversary of Bangladesh's independence from Pakistan in 1971.
   A government announcement said the release commemmorates the
18th anniversary Sunday.
   Among those released were 381 prisoners detained under the 1974
Special Powers Act, which allowed the government to detain suspects
for a year without trial.
   Opposition party members say the act mainly was used against
people within their ranks. The government of President Hussain
Muhammed has denied jailing people for political reasons.
</TEXT>
