<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Philippines-Rebels     03-25 0096</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Philippines-Rebels,0097</SECOND>
<HEAD>Report Troops Kill sSven Rebels In Running Gun Battle</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Soldiers killed seven rebels of the
Communist New People's Army during a running battle that extended
over 24 hours, the military reported Saturday.
   Lt. Col. Dionisio Santiago, an army provincial commander, said
the fighting began when rebels fired at an army patrol Wednesday on
the outskirts of the town of Maayon on Panay Island, 255 miles
southeast of Manila.
   Santiago said nine suspected guerrillas were captured during the
battle. He did not say if the government troops suffered any
casualties.
