entire villages, leaving tens of thousands homeless ... The first
day of the floods (Wednesday) alone left more than 50,000
destitute,'' he said.
   State-run Aden radio said Thursday that 154 houses and four
schools were destroyed in the Tarim region of the province, which
borders the Gulf of Aden.
   It referred to vast amounts of land and crops being washed away,
but made no mention of casualties.
   South Yemen's neighbors have begun relief shipments. King Fahd
of Saudi Arabia on Friday ordered the immediate dispatch of four
planeloads of tents, blankets, food and medical supplies to the
affected areas.
   The United Arab Emirates also sent relief supplies.
