<HEAD>Derailed Train Sparks Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A derailed train carrying a gasoline additive
erupted into flames in a freight yard Saturday, sending dark,
billowing smoke over a northeast Houston subdivision.
   A tanker loaded with heptane derailed as the train was being
linked at about 5 p.m. and took five other cars off the tracks. The
heptane may have been ignited by the grinding wheels, officials
said.
   No one was hurt in the blaze, said District Chief W.M. Whatley
of the Houston Fire Department.
